  "_about": "Anatomically Programmed Radiography (APR) chart. Selecting a protocol sets technique (kVp/mAs), anti-scatter grid, display LUT, SID, collimated field, and receptor size/orientation for that projection. Grouped body part -> region -> projection. Typical adult DR values: distal extremities 50-65 kVp no grid at 100 cm SID; proximal limb/skull/spine/abdomen/pelvis 70-90 kVp with grid at 100 cm; chest high-kVp 110-125 kVp with grid at 180 cm. coll = collimated field [width_cm, length_cm]; det = receptor [short_cm, long_cm]; orient = portrait/landscape. Teaching approximations, not a facility chart.",
